PSYC-532: Flipping graduate stat course

Andriy Koval
18-Sep-2015

Learning and Teaching Development Grant (LTDG)

Curriculum Needs

The curriculum revision by the Psychology Department recognized, among others, the following needs:

  1. R as the primary language of statistical computing
  2. Augment methodological training with practical data science skills

General Goals of the Project

  • to update and flip introductory graduaduate statistics course

Specific Goals of the Grant

  • production of interactive lessons with swirl
  • to adapt and to extend the existing collection of swirl courses

Progress Report

  • github repository as the course portal
  • professional library and defined scope of the course
  • comprehensive review of online resources
  • practice-oriented collection of tips and resources based on skill sets of data science
  • extendable timeline with key figures in the history of the discipline and the general history of science.
